  "prompt": "What are some reviews of the Sony Xperia C4?",
  "response": "The Sony Xperia C4, released in 2015, received mixed reviews from critics and users. Here\u2019s a summary of the common points highlighted in reviews:\n\n### **Positive Aspects:**\n1. **Design and Build Quality:**\n   - Praised for its sleek, modern design with a slim profile and rounded edges.\n   - The matte finish was appreciated for its premium feel and resistance to fingerprints.\n\n2. **Display:**\n   - The 5.5-inch Full HD IPS LCD screen was well-received for its vibrant colors and sharpness.\n   - Decent brightness and viewing angles were noted.\n\n3. **Selfie Camera:**\n   - The 5 MP front-facing camera with a soft LED flash was a standout feature, appealing to selfie enthusiasts.\n   - Good performance in low-light conditions due to the flash.\n\n4. **Performance:**\n   - The MediaTek MT6752 processor and 2GB RAM delivered smooth performance for everyday tasks.\n   - Handled multitasking and moderate gaming reasonably well.\n\n5. **Battery Life:**\n   - The 2600 mAh battery was considered decent for moderate usage, lasting a full day for most users.\n\n### **Negative Aspects:**\n1. **Main Camera:**\n   - The 13 MP rear camera was criticized for inconsistent performance, especially in low-light conditions.\n   - Lack of optical image stabilization and slow autofocus were common complaints.\n\n2. **Software:**\n   - The device launched with Android 5.0 Lollipop, which was seen as outdated by some users.\n   - Sony\u2019s custom UI was considered bloated by some reviewers.\n\n3. **Storage:**\n   - With only 16GB of internal storage (expandable via microSD), users felt limited, especially since a portion was taken up by the OS.\n\n4. **Price:**\n   - At its launch price, the Xperia C4 was seen as overpriced compared to competitors offering better specs for similar or lower prices.\n\n5. **Audio Quality:**\n   - While the loudspeaker was decent, some users found the audio output via headphones to be underwhelming.\n\n### **Overall Impression:**\nThe Sony Xperia C4 was viewed as a mid-range device with a focus on design and selfie capabilities. While it had some strong points, its camera performance, software, and pricing were seen as drawbacks. It appealed to users looking for a stylish phone with decent performance but fell short for those seeking better camera quality or value for money.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
